5. Given that paralysis and weakness on one side of the body are more directly related and more commonly co-occurring symptoms in brain hemorrhage patients, it is more likely that Marcus would experience these two symptoms together, rather than paralysis and altered sensorium.

Therefore, based on the information provided and the step-by-step analysis, the more likely scenario is (a) He also experiences weakness of one body side.
